-- India’s Nifty Futures Swing After Indexes Drop to One-Week Low
-- B y   S a n t a n u   C h a k r a b o r t y
-- 2013-11-07T01:51:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-07/india-s-nifty-futures-swing-after-indexes-drop-to-one-week-low.html
Indian (SENSEX)  stock-index futures swung
between gains and losses after benchmark indexes declined to the
lowest level in more than a week yesterday.  SGX CNX  Nifty (NIFTY)  Index futures for November delivery rose 0.1
percent to 6,261 at 9:32 a.m. in  Singapore . The underlying CNX
Nifty Index fell 0.6 percent to 6,215.15 yesterday. The S&P BSE
Sensex lost 0.4 percent to the lowest since Oct. 28. The Bank of
 New York  Mellon India ADR Index of U.S.-traded shares slid for a
sixth day, the longest losing streak since September 2012.  International investors were  net buyers  of Indian stocks
for a 22nd consecutive day on Nov. 5, according to data from the
market regulator. They purchased $4.9 billion of the nation’s
shares in the two months through Oct. 31, helping drive a 14
percent rally in the Sensex. Profits at 16 of the 20 companies
in the Sensex that have posted quarterly results so far exceeded
analyst estimates, compared with 47 percent that missed
forecasts in the previous quarter.  “We believe that the focus of the markets in the near term
will remain on global liquidity and quarterly results,” Dipen Shah, head of private client group research at Kotak Securities
Ltd., wrote in an e-mail.  The MSCI Asia Pacific Index fell today as investors await
economic data scheduled from the U.S. and amid concern gains in
stocks over the past two months have outpaced the prospects for
company earnings.  The Sensex has risen 7.6 percent this year and  trades  at
13.9 times projected 12-month profits, compared with the five-year average of 14.2 times. The MSCI  Emerging Markets  Index is
valued at 10.6 times earnings.  Overseas funds have invested $16.4 billion into Indian
shares in 2013, the most after Japan among 10 Asian markets
tracked by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
